[div class=p 
	"Shienryu is a video game, that much is true.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"This movie scores 156 Million points, the highest by a human (before closure of the game) is just under 70 million.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"This movie plays with the intention of getting as high of a score as possible (excluding manipulating something covered later)
	$LF
	"Like my previous submission of Daioh, This game might seem really similar! It's basically just Daioh again lol.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"But the scoring is far more involved, let's cover it.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"There exists a hidden multiplier mode that applies to all forms of score added to the counter, including shot points. It maxes at times 8 and only is active when you have NO LIVES LEFT and MISSILE WEAPON. (the worst one)
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Using a bomb cuts X amount of frames off of your current elapsed multiplier timer, meaning I am allowed to bomb, sometimes.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Saturn Version?
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Saturn version removes the *unlock* requirement for this mode present in the Arcade version; in the AC ver, you must have the 100th place score be above 3,000,000 points. and frankly this is just annoying, so I used the saturn port.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Scoring info :
	$LF
	"Ignoring x8 mode, what exists to earn points?
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Enemy kills, Tick points, reserve bombs on clearing stages, excess powerups and weapon pickups will all add to your score.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"There is a new addition in Shienryu compared to Daioh, and that is the LED items.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"These items drop at a random rate from any ground enemy and any flying enemy that can hit the ground. Red ones are equivalent to 1 LED, and Blues (far rarer) are 10. They are 500 points per LED in the stage clear bonus (x8 = 4,000)
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"If you're thinking I manipulated every single enemy to drop an LED, I admire your expectations of me! I really did try to manipulate extra LED's to spawn; especially blues. But I don't believe it is currently possible to have a 100% LED rate with TAS, so I manip'd the best I could.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"It should be mentioned, the drop rate for LED's is far higher in loop 2; so youll see some very high clear bonuses.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Enjoy Daioh-2!
	$LF
]div
